      "content": "i get that you're saying it's unlikely, but i've seen stuff online about how data can be hidden in audio signals using steganography. if someone wanted to influence people without getting caught, wouldn't using low-frequency modulation through a massive platform like spotify be the perfect way to do it? it would be so hard to prove. how would someone even go about shielding themselves from that kind of thing?",
